This paper deals with optimizing video delivery in a network, which involves resource allocation and quality adaptation. This suggests that it could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper specifically mentions the use of the DASH framework, which is a multimedia streaming protocol, indicating that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. The paper also mentions fairness and user preferences, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. The paper involves optimization, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. Finally, the paper deals with network resource allocation, which suggests that it could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category.
